==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Supererogation
<hw>Su`per*er`o*ga"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>supererogatio</ets> a payment in addition.]</ety> <def>The act of
supererogating; performance of more than duty or necessity
requires.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Works of supererogation</b></col> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld>,
<cd>those good deeds believed to have been performed by saints, or
capable of being performed by men, over and above what is required for
their own salvation.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supererogative</ent>⟦br⟧
